<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1538,2031]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1682,1707]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Matthews-Cascon et al., 1991" authorityName="Matthews-Cascon" authorityYear="1991" box="[324,860,1682,1707]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Latirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="260" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lacteum">
<emphasis box="[324,504,1682,1707]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Latirus lacteum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews-Cascon, H &amp; Matthews, H. R. &amp; Rocha, C. de" box="[514,860,1682,1707]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref28642" refString="Matthews-Cascon, H, Matthews, H. R. &amp; Rocha, C. de A. (1991) Nova especie de Latirus Montfort, 1810 (Mollusca: Gastropoda). Boletim do Museu Nacional, Rio de Janeiro, New Series, Zoologia, No. 349, 1 - 6." type="book chapter" year="1991">
Matthews-Cascon 
<emphasis box="[726,779,1682,1707]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">et al</emphasis>
., 1991
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was introduced for five specimens dredged from coralline algae substrates off Pará and 
<collectingRegion box="[588,672,1719,1743]" country="Brazil" name="Amapa" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Amapá</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[683,755,1718,1743]" name="Brazil" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. The description and figures resemble some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="260" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bernadensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">P. bernadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[356,527,1754,1779]" name="French Guiana" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
. We could not obtain specimens for comparison but obtained photographs of the 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1790,1815]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[267,404,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–38" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1763,1785]" captionTargetBox="[186,1408,193,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[186,1408,193,1748]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 17–38. Guianas Peristerniinae. 17–21. Lamellilatirus corrugatus n. sp. 17–19. Holotype, 30.5 mm, CP4381, 06°31’N, 52°26’W, depth 114–118 m, MNHN IM-2013-56529. 20–21. Paratype, 23.8 mm, CP 4380, MNHN IM-2012-20355; ANSP 473537. 22–26. Lamellilatirus boucheti n. sp., 22–24. Holotype, 23.1 mm, CP4381, 06°31’N, 52°26’W, depth 114–118 m, IM-2013-56530. 25–26. Paratype, 19.1 mm, same date as holotype, IM-2013-56531; ANSP 473538. 27–28. Polygona bernadensis (Bullock, 1974), 46.4 mm, CP 4402, 06˚18’N, 52.˚13.3’W, depth 95–97 m, MNHN IM-2013-56853. 29–38. Polygona lactea (Matthews-Cascon et al., 1991). 29–30. Holotype, 27 x 11 mm, Almirante Saldanha, sta. 1767, off Pará, Brazil, 01°32’05”N, 47°24’05”W, depth 63 m, MNRJ 6201. 31–32. Paratype, 18 x 8 mm, same data as holotype, CMPHRM- 668B. 33–34. Paratype, 32 x 14 mm, Almirante Saldanha sta. 2441, off Pará, 01°46’N, 47°14’W, depth not stated, CMPHRM- 1031B. 35–38. 25.5 and 29.5 mm, CP4352, 05°13.9’N, 51°41.7’W, depth 60 m, MNHN IM-2014-6078." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2637306/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Figs. 29–30</figureCitation>
) and two 
<typeStatus box="[524,631,1791,1815]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">paratypes</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[649,789,1790,1815]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–38" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1763,1785]" captionTargetBox="[186,1408,193,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[186,1408,193,1748]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 17–38. Guianas Peristerniinae. 17–21. Lamellilatirus corrugatus n. sp. 17–19. Holotype, 30.5 mm, CP4381, 06°31’N, 52°26’W, depth 114–118 m, MNHN IM-2013-56529. 20–21. Paratype, 23.8 mm, CP 4380, MNHN IM-2012-20355; ANSP 473537. 22–26. Lamellilatirus boucheti n. sp., 22–24. Holotype, 23.1 mm, CP4381, 06°31’N, 52°26’W, depth 114–118 m, IM-2013-56530. 25–26. Paratype, 19.1 mm, same date as holotype, IM-2013-56531; ANSP 473538. 27–28. Polygona bernadensis (Bullock, 1974), 46.4 mm, CP 4402, 06˚18’N, 52.˚13.3’W, depth 95–97 m, MNHN IM-2013-56853. 29–38. Polygona lactea (Matthews-Cascon et al., 1991). 29–30. Holotype, 27 x 11 mm, Almirante Saldanha, sta. 1767, off Pará, Brazil, 01°32’05”N, 47°24’05”W, depth 63 m, MNRJ 6201. 31–32. Paratype, 18 x 8 mm, same data as holotype, CMPHRM- 668B. 33–34. Paratype, 32 x 14 mm, Almirante Saldanha sta. 2441, off Pará, 01°46’N, 47°14’W, depth not stated, CMPHRM- 1031B. 35–38. 25.5 and 29.5 mm, CP4352, 05°13.9’N, 51°41.7’W, depth 60 m, MNHN IM-2014-6078." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2637306/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Figs. 31–34</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[865,972,1791,1815]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">paratypes</typeStatus>
are long-dead shells bearing polychaete tubes, foraminifera, and other encrustations, but the 
<typeStatus box="[749,850,1826,1851]" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">holotype</typeStatus>
, a shiny white shell, is fresh and in good condition except for an eroded protoconch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,1538,2031]" lastBlockId="22.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="261" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">
Specimens we include here as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" box="[559,660,1898,1923]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="260" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lactea">
<emphasis box="[559,573,1900,1923]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[591,660,1898,1923]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">lactea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are two empty white shells with broken lips and drill holes (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 17–38" captionStartId="17.[151,264,1763,1785]" captionTargetBox="[186,1408,193,1748]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[186,1408,193,1748]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURES 17–38. Guianas Peristerniinae. 17–21. Lamellilatirus corrugatus n. sp. 17–19. Holotype, 30.5 mm, CP4381, 06°31’N, 52°26’W, depth 114–118 m, MNHN IM-2013-56529. 20–21. Paratype, 23.8 mm, CP 4380, MNHN IM-2012-20355; ANSP 473537. 22–26. Lamellilatirus boucheti n. sp., 22–24. Holotype, 23.1 mm, CP4381, 06°31’N, 52°26’W, depth 114–118 m, IM-2013-56530. 25–26. Paratype, 19.1 mm, same date as holotype, IM-2013-56531; ANSP 473538. 27–28. Polygona bernadensis (Bullock, 1974), 46.4 mm, CP 4402, 06˚18’N, 52.˚13.3’W, depth 95–97 m, MNHN IM-2013-56853. 29–38. Polygona lactea (Matthews-Cascon et al., 1991). 29–30. Holotype, 27 x 11 mm, Almirante Saldanha, sta. 1767, off Pará, Brazil, 01°32’05”N, 47°24’05”W, depth 63 m, MNRJ 6201. 31–32. Paratype, 18 x 8 mm, same data as holotype, CMPHRM- 668B. 33–34. Paratype, 32 x 14 mm, Almirante Saldanha sta. 2441, off Pará, 01°46’N, 47°14’W, depth not stated, CMPHRM- 1031B. 35–38. 25.5 and 29.5 mm, CP4352, 05°13.9’N, 51°41.7’W, depth 60 m, MNHN IM-2014-6078." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2637306/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">Figs. 35–38</figureCitation>
); white seems to have been their original color and not a result of fading. Protoconch and teleoconch morphologies of the shells resemble those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" box="[692,859,1970,1995]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="260" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bernadensis">
<emphasis box="[692,706,1972,1995]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[724,859,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">bernadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the protoconchs are slightly smaller and the revolving cords of the spire are narrower than those of the latter species; many cords of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" box="[1148,1245,2006,2031]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="21" pageNumber="260" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lactea">
<emphasis box="[1148,1162,2007,2030]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1176,1245,2006,2031]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="260">lactea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are separated by single, finer threads in their interspaces. The net effect is of a shell that more resembles the original figures of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="261" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lactea">
<emphasis box="[1415,1429,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="261">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,219,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="261">lactea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than they do shells of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" box="[473,636,188,213]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="261" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bernadensis">
<emphasis box="[473,487,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="261">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[501,636,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="261">bernadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="261" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="22" pageNumber="261">
Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Vermeij &amp; Snyder" authorityYear="2006" box="[311,408,223,248]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fasciolariidae" genus="Polygona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="261" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lactea">
<emphasis box="[311,408,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="261">P. lactea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mallard, D. &amp; Robin, A." box="[566,860,223,248]" pageId="22" pageNumber="261" refId="ref28217" refString="Mallard, D. &amp; Robin, A. (2005) Fasciolariidae. Museum du Coquillage, Les Sables d'Olonne, 27 pp., 70 pls." type="book" year="2005">Mallard and Robin (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, it was not included in the compendium by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mallard, D. &amp; Robin, A." pageId="22" pageNumber="261" refId="ref28246" refString="Mallard, D. &amp; Robin, A. (2017) Recent Fasciolariidae. AFC, Paris and ConchBooks, Harxheim. 349 pp." type="book" year="2017">Mallard and Robin (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. Very few specimens are known, and the original specimens seem to have been immature and in less than optimal condition. Perhaps fresher mature specimens could enable better understanding of this poorly known species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
